From: OpenWrt Build System <openwrt@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] qca-nss-dp: split EDMA v1 Rx and Tx NAPI

Move legacy EDMA v1 receive and Tx completion handling to independent
NAPI contexts so their budgets and interrupt masks no longer interfere.
Expose GRO as an optional feature and enable it by default.

Also correct IRQ unwind, descriptor indexing and DMA mapping lifetime
issues found while auditing the QSDK data path. Hardware checksum offload
is not advertised because the v1 descriptor format has no verified
checksum fields.

Signed-off-by: OpenWrt Build System <openwrt@localhost>
